node.text:
I think for me my goal body has shifted. I make goals with my body. Not for my body.
Not anymore, at least. 

For instance: 
I want to swim with my babies. 
I want to hug without thinking about what that person is thinking about my waist. 
I want to wear clothes I like. 
I want to model and dance and make a fool of myself. 
I want to move in ways that makes me happy. 
I want to see the world around me! Really see it. 
I want to eat food and enjoy it, fearlessly. 

Measurements of joy. 
Instead of measurements of my body. 

I want to live a life with my body not against it. 

That is my goal. 
I’m not fully there! 
And that’s ok! 

I’m working towards it. 
And it’s different from old goals I use to have.

But every time I keep stepping into it all, the better it gets. 

🤍

Thought prompts thanks fo a recent post from  @kenziebrenna that unlocked a memory of an old pinterest board I used to have of my “goal body”. None of those images ever showed me a life they lived, just how they looked. I know that now. I’m working through it now.

node.text:
Woven within our very skin is the magic to change and adapt.

We were built for this. 
So that we do not break from this. 

Down to the very layers of who we are, 
we stretch, we grow, we become. 

So when it happens, as it does, that the guilt and doubt and shame creep in… 
as you slide your hands across the new textures and shapes and let the emotions flow as you do… 

Never forget the ✨magic✨

We were built for this. 
So that we do not break from this. 

And that some people,
just don’t believe in magic.

node.text:
I find my shame lives in little pocket moments. The moments nobody sees but it’s all I can see. 

Lately I’ve caught myself changing in the bathroom to avoid being seen. 

A shame pocket. 
For the way my body looks when I get dressed. 

But yesterday I went into the shame pocket and looked around a bit. 

I thought it was funny and maybe even cute how my squishy self could squish itself into a favourite dress. 
I realized there’s still a lot of layers of myself I’m working on from the inside out, lessons to learn or unlearn. 

I thought it was sweet how when I expressed my struggles with my soft sagging stretched body to my husband he said “you know that’s really normal right?” (Yeah, I do, I talk about it on the internet everyday…but here I am).

Shame pockets for me are quite small blips these days. 
They used to be much bigger. 
Much stickier to get out of. 
Much more time consuming. 

But I know how shame breeds. It breeds in secrecy and darkness. 
It doesn’t quite have a place to grip when it’s out in the world. When you talk about it. When you allow yourself the processing. 

So that’s what this is. A little peek inside a shame pocket, that I don’t want to get bigger. 

A reminder that these intimate moments with yourself can be hard but be magical too. 

And listen. I do think pictures like these are a bit problematic. They perpetuate that hidden fat is better and safer and can sometimes protect our feelings around fat or body change. 
But I also know it’s a dang awful feeling to be hiding out in your body thinking you’re the only one. So I see both. I’m working on myself within these pockets of shame too for both. 

So that one day I just change my clothes and watch my body squish and squeeze and I just move the eff on. I respect it. 
No pockets at all. 
(The only time no pockets is acceptable).
